1
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:17,367
I'm not scared anymore
because I know you're there,

2
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:20,333
Grandmother Ligaya,
Mom, and Dad.

3
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:21,733
Did you see that, Astrid?

4
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:23,567
Emma and Mookie mare so happy.

5
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:27,200
I am Mookie's mother,
and I won't lose.

6
00:00:27,267 --> 00:00:29,600
We'll find a way to arrest
Ms. Caparas,

7
00:00:29,667 --> 00:00:31,167
especially since you have solid
evidence and testimony

8
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:32,067
from your witnesses.
Hello?

9
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,667
I won't let the police arrest
me.

10
00:00:34,767 --> 00:00:36,033
Olive, where are you going?

11
00:00:36,100 --> 00:00:39,667
I know you still love Olive
despite how she is.

12
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:43,200
But she needs to pay for
the wrong things she did.

13
00:00:43,267 --> 00:00:45,267
You have nothing
to apologize for.

14
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:46,600
Ma'am! Get in!

15
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:50,933
Mommy has to pay for all the
sins she committed against you.

16
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:51,700
Who are you?

17
00:00:51,767 --> 00:00:52,800
Hi, Mookie.

18
00:00:52,867 --> 00:00:54,667
It's time to go home.

19
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:42,967
Nurse, where's the patient
on this bed?

20
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:46,367
Her grandmother brought her
to the garden.

21
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:48,267
She didn't tell me that.

22
00:01:50,433 --> 00:01:51,467
I'll go and see them.

23
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:00,700
Okay, bye.

24
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:05,133
Mookie?

25
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:07,933
Mookie!

26
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,400
Mommy, wait.
Where are you taking me?

27
00:02:17,867 --> 00:02:18,933
Be quiet.

28
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,800
Emma might hear you.

29
00:02:20,867 --> 00:02:23,100
She might steal you
from me again.

30
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:26,200
We'll be together again.
I'll take you home.

31
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:28,300
No, Mommy. I don't want
to go with you.

32
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:30,633
Mommy, bring me back
to Mommy Emma. Please.

33
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:31,667
No!

34
00:02:31,733 --> 00:02:34,267
You're not getting better
with them.

35
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:36,533
You're getting worse.

36
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,433
They're crazy.

37
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,867
They're giving you all sorts
of medicines.

38
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:43,267
No, Mommy.

39
00:02:44,433 --> 00:02:46,733
You're the one who does that.

40
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:49,500
You're the one who's sick.

41
00:02:49,567 --> 00:02:52,800
Mookie, don't be stubborn.

42
00:02:52,867 --> 00:02:54,600
Listen to your mother.

43
00:02:55,867 --> 00:02:57,833
No. No, no!

44
00:02:57,900 --> 00:02:58,467
Mookie!

45
00:02:58,533 --> 00:02:59,767
I don't want that!

46
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:00,567
Mookie!
Mom!

47
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:04,667
Why didn't you tell me you'd
bring Mookie outside?

48
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:07,533
Mookie's missing, dear.

49
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,733
What?

50
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,600
Where?
Where's Mookie?

51
00:03:11,967 --> 00:03:14,767
Kid, did you see
my granddaughter earlier?

52
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,333
Is she the young girl
in the wheelchair?

53
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,300
Yes.

54
00:03:17,367 --> 00:03:19,000
I saw a female doctor wheeled
her out.

55
00:03:19,067 --> 00:03:19,867
Female doctor?

56
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:22,167
Mom! Let's look for her!

57
00:03:22,267 --> 00:03:23,533
My God!

58
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,667
Mookie!

59
00:03:36,367 --> 00:03:40,933
Olive! Why are you ignoring
my calls?

60
00:03:43,467 --> 00:03:46,867
Mister, are we almost
at Ladera Medical Center?

61
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:50,367
Yes, Ma'am. But there's traffic
on the way.

62
00:03:50,433 --> 00:03:52,533
We'll take the alternative
route.

63
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:55,533
What if I walk from here?

64
00:03:55,633 --> 00:03:56,733
Is it possible?

65
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,867
Yes, Ma'am.

66
00:03:57,933 --> 00:03:59,033
Okay, Mister.

67
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,300
Please pull over.

68
00:04:00,367 --> 00:04:01,400
Okay.

69
00:04:02,633 --> 00:04:05,267
I wonder where Olive is.

70
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:07,100
Maybe you should've come
with her.

71
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:11,133
Someone might recognize me.

72
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:14,167
I'm actually nervous about
what Olive's plan.

73
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:17,333
Get in the car.

74
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,533
So we're ready in case
she needs our help.

75
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:20,533
Go.

76
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:25,700
Olive!
Olive, come here.

77
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:27,500
Come here.

78
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:30,900
Why do you look like that?

79
00:04:30,967 --> 00:04:33,100
Is that your disguise?

80
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,800
Did you execute your plan?

81
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:39,200
Did you get Mookie
from the hospital?

82
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:40,633
What did you say?

83
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:46,200
Olive is planning to get Mookie?

84
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:48,300
What?

85
00:04:48,367 --> 00:04:50,200
OMG!

86
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:51,500
Are you Astrid?

87
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,867
Jade?

88
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:55,700
Yes.

89
00:04:56,733 --> 00:05:00,567
So Olive has a plan
to kidnap Mookie.

90
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:02,967
As if it's not enough
that she took Mookie

91
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:04,500
from her parents before.

92
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:09,600
And she also did to Mookie
what she did to me.

93
00:05:09,667 --> 00:05:11,667
She locked her up, too.

94
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:12,967
Where's Olive?

95
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,700
I don't know.

96
00:05:15,767 --> 00:05:20,100
If you're here and Olive
plan to get Mookie

97
00:05:20,167 --> 00:05:21,700
from the hospital,

98
00:05:21,767 --> 00:05:24,533
that means Olive is here, too.

99
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,967
You're waiting for her.

100
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:28,800
Mommy, please!

101
00:05:28,867 --> 00:05:30,900
That's the reason you
get harmed.

102
00:05:30,967 --> 00:05:32,767
You don't listen to me.

103
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:38,933
Help! Help! Guard, help!

104
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,600
Olive!

105
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,933
Help me, please!

106
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,633
Go ahead. Try to make a noise.

107
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:53,400
And I'll remove your voice box.

108
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:54,867
I said be quiet!

109
00:05:57,767 --> 00:05:58,600
Help!

110
00:05:59,767 --> 00:06:00,533
Shut up.

111
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:08,267
Miss! Miss!
Did you see a female patient?

112
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:09,367
She's in a wheelchair.

113
00:06:09,433 --> 00:06:12,500
No, but there's a hostage-taking
going on outside.

114
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:13,367
Mom, come on!

115
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:14,467
Mookie!

116
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,567
You're so evil.

117
00:06:18,633 --> 00:06:20,367
- Mookie, dear!
- You're so evil.

118
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:24,133
There she is.
The woman who'll kill you.

119
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:27,033
- Let go of my daughter.
- Go ahead!

120
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:33,733
I dare you to come near us if
you want to see this kid bleed.

121
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,567
What?

122
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,033
Don't come near.

123
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:43,100
Don't startle me.

124
00:06:43,167 --> 00:06:45,267
I might stab Mookie.

125
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:48,967
Olive, I'm begging you.

126
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,800
Mookie is your daughter, too.

127
00:06:52,867 --> 00:06:55,233
And I know you love Mookie.

128
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:59,100
Show us you love her.
Be a mother to her.

129
00:06:59,167 --> 00:07:01,400
You should've thought
of that before.

130
00:07:02,633 --> 00:07:04,200
I loved Mookie.

131
00:07:05,267 --> 00:07:07,467
But what did you do?

132
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:10,533
I almost gave up my whole life
for her.

133
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,500
But what did you do?

134
00:07:12,567 --> 00:07:14,433
You took her away from me.

135
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:18,633
I suffered longer
because you took my child.

136
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:20,333
My child is only mine!

137
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:23,433
Please give her to us
if you still have mercy

138
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:28,033
and love left for her.
I'm begging you, Olive!

139
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:28,767
No!

140
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:34,767
Olive! Olive, stop! Stop!

141
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:38,500
Olive, please.

142
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:41,467
Have mercy on Mookie.

143
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:46,233
What are you doing here?

144
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:47,967
Olive, please stop.

145
00:07:48,067 --> 00:07:52,033
You're already doing something
bad. Stop it.

146
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,700
Stay out of it!

147
00:07:53,767 --> 00:07:55,667
I'm sorry, Olive.

148
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:58,633
But I can't give you
what you want.

149
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,533
Get out of here!

150
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,933
I said go!

151
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,067
No, Olive.

152
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,133
I'm not going anywhere.

153
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:09,367
Because I won't let you
turn into an evil person.

154
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:11,700
Because I care about you!

155
00:08:12,733 --> 00:08:14,467
I love you, Olive.

156
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:18,900
I love you
because you're my sister.

157
00:08:18,967 --> 00:08:20,800
We're twins.

158
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:31,667
Oh, you have a twin?

159
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:33,933
What a pity!

160
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,833
The world has crazies like you.

161
00:08:37,367 --> 00:08:39,533
Exactly, Jade!

162
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:40,900
We're twins!

163
00:08:40,967 --> 00:08:42,800
We're sisters!

164
00:08:42,867 --> 00:08:46,200
And yet you choose to take
someone else's side over mine!

165
00:08:46,267 --> 00:08:49,833
I can't enable you anymore
with this!

166
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:51,533
This is already wrong!

167
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,700
Please!

168
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:55,067
Please, don't hurt Mookie.

169
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:57,300
Give her back to her mother.

170
00:08:57,367 --> 00:08:58,667
No!

171
00:08:58,733 --> 00:09:00,633
No!

172
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,467
Mookie is only mine.

173
00:09:02,533 --> 00:09:04,367
She's only mine!

174
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:05,467
Olive, please.

175
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:06,767
Please.

176
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:10,200
Let's talk this over as sisters!

177
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:11,367
No!

178
00:09:11,433 --> 00:09:14,033
I know you'll just take
their side!

179
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:16,933
Because you don't care about me,
Jade!

180
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,900
You left me!

181
00:09:18,967 --> 00:09:22,500
You left me alone, Jade!
You abandoned me!

182
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:25,767
Because you took advantage
of my weakness!

183
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:27,533
You manipulated me!

184
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,167
Used me!

185
00:09:29,267 --> 00:09:34,133
No, I only did that I was
concerned about you.

186
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:37,267
You gave me all sorts of drugs.

187
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:40,833
You controlled me using
those drugs.

188
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:44,133
You're the reason
I became a junkie.

189
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:47,033
So you're a pusher, too.

190
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:52,367
And I won't let you
do that to Mookie, too!

191
00:09:52,433 --> 00:09:54,100
So, please!

192
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:55,500
Have mercy on her.

193
00:09:55,567 --> 00:09:58,400
I won't let you do
the same thing to her!

194
00:09:58,467 --> 00:09:59,633
Shut up!

195
00:10:03,733 --> 00:10:06,300
Oh my God.
Plot twist of the year.

196
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:10,067
Olive Caparas has a twin sister.

197
00:10:10,133 --> 00:10:14,433
But just like the twin stories,
Olive is the evil one.

198
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:18,100
Oh my God. What can you say
about that? Comment down below.

199
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:19,433
Stop lying, Jade!

200
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:22,800
I didn't abuse you.

201
00:10:22,867 --> 00:10:26,667
You needed comfort,
and that's what I gave you.

202
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:30,800
I only did what I thought
was right back then.

203
00:10:32,867 --> 00:10:36,067
And that's also what
I'll do for Mookie.

204
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:41,967
If needed, I will do anything.
If that will make us both happy,

205
00:10:42,033 --> 00:10:43,233
I will do it.

206
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:48,500
Olive, we all know you love
Mookie like your own child.

207
00:10:48,567 --> 00:10:52,933
Not just like my own child.
She is really my daughter!

208
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,733
Look at Mookie.

209
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:58,200
She's getting choked.
Her neck is already bleeding!

210
00:10:58,267 --> 00:11:00,367
Have mercy on her!

211
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:06,767
Is that how you treat someone
you love?

212
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,333
Do you think she's happy?

213
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,467
Olive, stop!

214
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:12,600
Mookie.

215
00:11:12,667 --> 00:11:17,000
Mookie, I'm so sorry.

216
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:20,033
I'm so sorry if I'm hurting you,
sweetie.

217
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:24,300
It's just that your mommy
loves you so much, Mookie.

218
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:26,100
I'm so sorry.

219
00:11:26,167 --> 00:11:30,433
Mommy, love shouldn't hurt.

220
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:31,767
Love is not selfish.

221
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,367
No, no.

222
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:41,133
If I have to be selfish for you,
I'll do so.

223
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,667
I'll do so, Mookie.

224
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:52,167
Send help. Mookie is bleeding.

225
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:56,400
Mommy.

226
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:58,167
Mommy, please.

227
00:11:58,233 --> 00:12:01,133
Give me back to Mommy Emma.

228
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,600
Please.

229
00:12:02,667 --> 00:12:05,867
Mommy Emma!
Mommy Emma!

230
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:08,567
You talk about nothing but Emma!

231
00:12:08,633 --> 00:12:09,467
Mommy, please.

232
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:10,967
Why?

233
00:12:11,033 --> 00:12:13,967
Why do you choose
that woman over me?

234
00:12:15,467 --> 00:12:18,933
I can give you the love
she's giving you.

235
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,667
I'll give you even more
than that, Mookie.

236
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:24,067
More than that.

237
00:12:24,133 --> 00:12:26,267
I don't want that, Mommy!

238
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,200
Why?

239
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:33,633
Is the love I'm giving you
not enough?

240
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:39,300
Why do people always leave me?

241
00:12:39,367 --> 00:12:41,200
Mookie.

242
00:12:41,267 --> 00:12:43,667
First, my parents.

243
00:12:43,733 --> 00:12:46,433
And then my ex. And then you!

244
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,033
You all left me.

245
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:57,233
Haven't you thought I have
so much love to give and get!

246
00:12:58,967 --> 00:13:03,333
You're wasting that. You, too.

247
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:08,900
Because your love
is suffocating, Olive.

248
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:14,000
You're choking everyone around
you because of your love!

249
00:13:14,067 --> 00:13:15,767
No!

250
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,400
You're a liar!

251
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:19,600
Olive.

252
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:23,900
They're right.

253
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:28,533
Please, Mommy.
Stop this, please.

254
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:32,667
A lot of people have been hurt.
Don't you see it?

255
00:13:32,733 --> 00:13:34,267
No, Mookie.

256
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:38,900
I won't stop until I get you.

257
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:45,767
- Emma, don't.
- Go ahead!

258
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:54,700
- Olive!
- Emma!

259
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:58,533
I dare you to get Mookie!

260
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,333
She'll bleed here!

261
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,667
Mom!

262
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:03,700
Don't hurt my granddaughter!

263
00:14:03,767 --> 00:14:06,133
- Mookie!
- Dear!

264
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:08,100
Mookie!
Emma!

265
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:09,467
Where's Mookie?

266
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,167
Where's the hostage?

267
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:12,767
Go and catch them!

268
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:14,100
I'll get the car!

269
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:15,367
Hurry!

270
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:17,533
Mom.

271
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:19,867
Excuse me.

272
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:23,133
I'm Jade.

273
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,100
I want to help you.

274
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:26,700
I'll go with you.

275
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,200
Wait.

276
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,800
You're going to help us?

277
00:14:32,967 --> 00:14:36,000
What if you're working
with your crazy sister?

278
00:14:36,067 --> 00:14:37,600
And kill us?

279
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:38,467
No.

280
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:43,800
Honestly, I disagree with what
my sister does.

281
00:14:45,067 --> 00:14:48,700
I actually want to ask for
your forgiveness on her behalf

282
00:14:48,767 --> 00:14:53,033
for taking Mookie and everything
she did to you.

283
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:55,133
I don't believe you.

284
00:14:56,167 --> 00:14:57,467
Why would you help us?

285
00:14:58,667 --> 00:15:00,767
Are we related to you?

286
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:03,867
Oh, you said she turned you into
a junkie.

287
00:15:03,967 --> 00:15:06,567
Are you going to take revenge
against her?

288
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:10,467
Olive did a lot more than that.

289
00:15:11,867 --> 00:15:15,833
She deprived me of my share
in our properties and money.

290
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:20,200
I'll help you because I also
want her to pay

291
00:15:20,267 --> 00:15:22,167
for everything she did to me.

292
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,800
Mom, come on. Get in!

293
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:30,067
Let's go.

294
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:32,000
If you're coming with us,
let's go.

295
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:33,500
We have no time.

296
00:15:38,733 --> 00:15:39,767
Let's go, Ando.

297
00:15:42,033 --> 00:15:43,700
Mommy.

298
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:47,233
Mommy, please.
Just take me back to them.

299
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:49,600
Can you stop, Mookie?

300
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:52,100
Why do you always get me mad?

301
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:56,733
You're always mad at me.

302
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:03,233
I feel like I'm a horrible
person because of you.

303
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,500
Of course not, Mookie.

304
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:06,867
That's not true.

305
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:18,233
Mommy, you're wounded.

306
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:22,667
No, I'm fine.
Don't worry about me.

307
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:25,533
I'm more worried about
your wound.

308
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:26,500
Don't worry.

309
00:16:26,567 --> 00:16:28,733
I'll treat it as soon
as we get home.

310
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,233
I'll treat it.

311
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:36,300
Ma'am, a van is following us.

312
00:16:36,367 --> 00:16:37,100
What?

313
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:42,833
- Ando, drive faster!
- Mommy Emma!

314
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:44,500
Hurry! They're chasing us!

315
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:46,567
Shut up, Mookie!

316
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:47,800
Stop it!

317
00:16:47,867 --> 00:16:48,967
Ando, faster!

318
00:16:51,967 --> 00:16:53,567
Mommy Emma!

319
00:16:53,633 --> 00:16:54,967
Mookie, what are you doing?
Stop it!

320
00:16:55,033 --> 00:16:55,833
Mommy Emma!

321
00:16:55,900 --> 00:16:57,500
I'll cut your hand off!

322
00:16:57,567 --> 00:16:58,200
Mommy Emma!
Stop it!

323
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:01,500
Dan, drive faster!

324
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:03,933
- Faster!
- I'm driving fast, Emma.

325
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:07,567
- Mommy Emma!
- Stop! Stop it, Mookie!

326
00:17:07,633 --> 00:17:09,033
What are you doing? Mommy Emma!

327
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:13,167
- Won't you really stop?
- Mom! Mom!

328
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:25,867
Can't you go any faster, Ando?

329
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:27,667
We might lose them!

330
00:17:27,733 --> 00:17:31,000
- I'm on it! Their car is fast.
- Faster, Dan!

331
00:17:31,067 --> 00:17:34,033
Ma'am, can't they follow us
where we're going?

332
00:17:35,567 --> 00:17:39,467
Only you and Astrid know
that place.

333
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:41,900
I'm sure they can't follow us
there.

334
00:17:46,567 --> 00:17:48,000
Sleep well, Mookie.

335
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:52,433
We're almost home, sweetheart.

336
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:02,200
Hello, Astrid.

337
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:04,800
Thank you for sending bodyguards
over here.

338
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:07,433
I'll call you
when I need something.

339
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,167
Mommy?

340
00:18:12,333 --> 00:18:13,300
Mookie!

341
00:18:16,133 --> 00:18:17,467
You're finally awake.

342
00:18:18,633 --> 00:18:21,967
Mommy, where am I?

343
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:23,567
We're finally home.

344
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:27,500
From now on, we'll live here
peacefully.

345
00:18:27,567 --> 00:18:29,633
Where no one can mess with us.

346
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:30,767
I don't want to.

347
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:33,433
Mommy, I don't want to be here.
Mommy!

348
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,667
- Mommy, I don't want it here!
- Stay still.

349
00:18:35,733 --> 00:18:38,767
- Mommy, I said no!
- What's wrong with you?

350
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:41,900
I'm helping you, and yet you're
being ungrateful!

351
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:43,767
I don't need your treatment!

352
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:47,433
You're a fake doctor.
Aren't you?

353
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:51,733
Instead of making me better,
you're making my illness worse!

354
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,467
How dare you question me!

355
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,900
You have nowhere to go, Mookie.

356
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,533
So, just accept that we'll be
together forever!

357
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,233
- I don't want to!
- No!

358
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:03,800
You're gonna be with me forever!

359
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:04,567
I don't want to!

360
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:13,300
I'm so sorry.

361
00:19:13,367 --> 00:19:17,933
I'm so sorry for hurting you,
sweetie. It's your fault.

362
00:19:19,233 --> 00:19:22,367
Why do you always pick a fight
with me?

363
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:24,067
Mookie, what else?

364
00:19:24,133 --> 00:19:25,767
- What do I need to do?
- Nothing.

365
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:29,433
Nothing, Mommy.
You don't have to do anything.

366
00:19:29,533 --> 00:19:32,767
Do you want me to be lenient?

367
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:36,300
- Do you want dolls? Gadgets?
- No.

368
00:19:36,367 --> 00:19:37,267
Do you want me to buy you
gadgets? Toys?

369
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:38,567
No, I don't want that.

370
00:19:38,633 --> 00:19:41,467
What about the food you want
to eat that I forbid?

371
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:44,567
- No. I don't want that.
- Ice cream? Chips? Candies?

372
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:45,900
- I'll give them all to you.
- I don't want that.

373
00:19:45,967 --> 00:19:47,167
I'll give you everything you
want.

374
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:49,933
I don't want that, Mommy.
I said no!

375
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:53,900
Do you want us to go out?
Let's watch a movie.

376
00:19:53,967 --> 00:19:54,667
We can do that.

377
00:19:54,733 --> 00:19:57,767
Mommy, I said I don't want that!

378
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:00,700
I don't need any of those!

379
00:20:00,767 --> 00:20:02,100
I don't need ice cream.

380
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,500
I don't need gadgets.

381
00:20:03,567 --> 00:20:05,200
I don't want anything
that you offer.

382
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:06,533
I don't need you!

383
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:13,000
You're giving me a hard time.

384
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:14,733
What's wrong with you?

385
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,567
What else do you want?

386
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:18,033
Mommy Emma!

387
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:22,933
No!

388
00:20:26,567 --> 00:20:28,667
Send more people
to the ancestral house.

389
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:32,400
I have a good feeling that Emma
and Jade will go there.

390
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:36,233
They don't know each other,
but they have one common enemy.

391
00:20:36,333 --> 00:20:37,767
And that's me.

392
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:40,067
She experiments on her.

393
00:20:40,133 --> 00:20:41,300
She plays with her.

394
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:46,000
She did the same thing to me,
so I would depend on her.

395
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:47,933
You two look so cute
in that picture.

396
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,233
It reminds me of my twins.

397
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:52,267
Twins?

398
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,500
We're back to our normal life.

399
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:58,600
You are my patient.

400
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:01,467
And I am your doctor.

401
00:21:01,533 --> 00:21:06,133
And this time, I'll make sure we
won't get separated again.

402
00:21:07,633 --> 00:21:12,067
I've longed for her for years.
We can't lose her again.
